simplesect.title: Description
simplesect.para: Initialize the table that the OS loader uses to keep track of information about objects

simplesect.title: Description
simplesect.para: Find the Address of a Symbol

parameterdescription.para: symbol_address cpuaddr Pointer to symbol with passed name

entry.para: OS_INVALID_POINTER if the pointer passed in is invalid

simplesect.title: Description
simplesect.para: Dumps the system symbol table to a file

parameterdescription.para: Name of file to write to
size_limit uint32 Size limit of file

entry.para: #OS_INVALID_FILE if the file could not be opened or written

simplesect.title: Description
simplesect.para: Loads an object file into the running operating system

parameterdescription.para: Name of file to write to

entry.para: OS_INVALID_POINTER if the pointer passed in is invalid
OS_ERR_NAME_TAKEN if the name is in use
OS_ERR_NO_FREE_IDS if the module table is full

simplesect.title: Description
simplesect.para: Unloads the module file from the running operating system

parameterdescription.para: uint32 ID of module to unload

simplesect.title: Description
simplesect.para: Returns information about the loadable module

parameterdescription.para: Name of file to write to

entry.para: OS_ERR_INVALID_ID if the module id invalid
OS_INVALID_POINTER if the pointer passed in is invalid
